  "texts": [
    "It brings serious data imbalance for this bi-label learning problem and degenerates the performance of the scorer.",
    "To address this problem, we propose a data-imbalance-aware bi-label learning algorithm in the next section.4.2.2 Data-imbalance-aware Bi-label Learning.",
    "To alleviate the impact of data imbalance, we propose to give different weights for different data and automatically learn the weights with hypergradient-descent [1,2].",
    "The weighted loss is given as follows.𝐿(𝜃, 𝐷) =1 |𝐷 | ∑︁ (𝑥,𝑦) ∈𝐷 [𝑓 (𝑤) • 𝑙 (ℎ(𝑥, 𝜃), 𝑦)](2)where𝑓 (𝑤) = 𝑤𝛿 𝑦 1,𝑦 2 + (1 -𝑤)(1 -𝛿 𝑦 1,𝑦 2), (𝑦 1, 𝑦 2) ∈ 𝑦.",
    "(3)In the above equation, 𝑤 is the weight, and 𝛿 𝑦 1,𝑦 2 is the Kronecker delta which is 1 when 𝑦 1 is equal to 𝑦 2 and 0 otherwise."
  ],
